  Locus:
    Page: 33
    Verse: 15
Tags:
  - Belief
---
We are incredibly heedless in the formation of our beliefs, but find
ourselves with an illicit passion for them when anyone proposes to rob us
of their companionship. It is obviously not the ideas themselves that are
dear to us, but our self-esteem that is threatened.
